727E             7 432 ; Check adjacent hexagons.
727E             7 433 ;
727E             7 434 ; This is an approach to update the two-distance of adjacent positions. As explained in Jack van Rijswijck's thesis:
727E             7 435 ; "two cells are adjacent if they share a common edge on the board."
727E             7 436 ;
727E             7 437 ; Input:    E  = current position
727E             7 438 ;           C  = current distance (with a flag at 6th bit that indicates a friendly position)
727E             7 439 ;           HL = current edge position address (a flag in 7th bit indicates an edge position and the lowest 3 bits the
727E             7 440 ;                edge number)
727E             7 441 ;
727E             7 442 ; Output:   A  = 0 and HL = cyan or red queue head address, if there is a chain of connected tokens of the same color
727E             7 443 ;                between the two edges.
